{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "tourky-admin-trips-collection",
    "name": "Tourky - Admin Trips APIs",
    "description": "Admin portal trip flow tests.\n\nRun order:\n1) Admin Login\n2) Get Grouped Pending Reservations — `data` is **date → time_id → reservations**; sets `trip_date` + `trip_time_id` from the first group\n3) Create Trip — **2 cars** (default test; needs enough pending seats & distinct captains/cars in variables)\n3b) Create Trip — **1 car** (smaller groups)\n4) List Trips\n5) Show Trip\n6) Update Trip (>24h before start)\n7) Delete Trip (>24h before start)\n\nCollection variables: `captain_id`, `car_id`, `captain_id_2`, `car_id_2` must exist in your DB (different captains & cars).\n\nIf your seeded admin password is `123456`, keep default.\nSet `baseUrl` to your backend API root, for example: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api" },
    { "key": "admin_phone", "value": "01000000001" },
    { "key": "admin_password", "value": "123456" },
    { "key": "admin_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "trip_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "trip_time_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "trip_date", "value": "" },
    { "key": "captain_id", "value": "2" },
    { "key": "car_id", "value": "1" },
    { "key": "captain_id_2", "value": "3" },
    { "key": "car_id_2", "value": "2" },
    { "key": "per_page", "value": "10" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1) Admin Login",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Token exists', function () { pm.expect(j.token).to.be.a('string'); });",
              "if (j.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', j.token);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"{{admin_phone}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{admin_password}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/login"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2) Get Grouped Pending Reservations",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Has grouped data', function () { pm.expect(j.data).to.be.an('object'); });",
              "const dateKeys = Object.keys(j.data || {});",
              "pm.test('At least one date exists', function () { pm.expect(dateKeys.length).to.be.greaterThan(0); });",
              "if (dateKeys.length) {",
              "  const date = dateKeys[0];",
              "  const byTime = j.data[date] || {};",
              "  pm.test('Nested by time_id', function () { pm.expect(byTime).to.be.an('object'); });",
              "  const timeKeys = Object.keys(byTime);",
              "  pm.test('At least one date+time group', function () { pm.expect(timeKeys.length).to.be.greaterThan(0); });",
              "  if (timeKeys.length) {",
              "    const timeId = timeKeys[0];",
              "    const firstGroup = byTime[timeId] || [];",
              "    if (firstGroup.length && firstGroup[0].time_id) {",
              "      pm.collectionVariables.set('trip_date', date);",
              "      pm.collectionVariables.set('trip_time_id', String(firstGroup[0].time_id));",
              "    }",
              "  }",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "bearer",
          "bearer": [
            { "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }
          ]
        },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/reservations"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3) Create Trip",
      "description": "Requires `trip_date` + `trip_time_id` from step 2 (or set them manually).\n\nBody uses `cars`: each entry is one vehicle (captain + car). Two cars is the typical case when pending reservations exceed one vehicle's seats.\n\nAdjust `captain_id`, `car_id`, `captain_id_2`, `car_id_2` in collection variables to match your DB (distinct captains and cars).",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const date = pm.collectionVariables.get('trip_date');",
              "const timeId = pm.collectionVariables.get('trip_time_id');",
              "if (!date || String(date).trim() === '') {",
              "  console.warn('[Create Trip] trip_date is empty — run step 2 first or set collection variable trip_date.');",
              "}",
              "if (!timeId || String(timeId).trim() === '') {",
              "  console.warn('[Create Trip] trip_time_id is empty — run step 2 first or set collection variable trip_time_id.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 201', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "pm.test('Content-Type JSON', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/json'); });",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Success envelope', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('success');",
              "  pm.expect(j.message).to.be.a('string');",
              "});",
              "pm.test('Created trip object', function () { pm.expect(j.data).to.be.an('object'); });",
              "pm.test('Trip has id, date, time_id, status', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(j.data).to.have.property('id');",
              "  pm.expect(j.data).to.have.property('date');",
              "  pm.expect(j.data).to.have.property('time_id');",
              "  pm.expect(j.data).to.have.property('status');",
              "});",
              "pm.test('Has cars array', function () { pm.expect(j.data.cars).to.be.an('array'); });",
              "pm.test('Two vehicles in response', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(j.data.cars.length).to.eql(2);",
              "});",
              "pm.test('Each car has captain, car, clients, reservations_count', function () {",
              "  j.data.cars.forEach(function (row) {",
              "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('id');",
              "    pm.expect(row.captain).to.be.an('object');",
              "    pm.expect(row.captain).to.have.property('id');",
              "    pm.expect(row.car).to.be.an('object');",
              "    pm.expect(row.car).to.have.property('id');",
              "    pm.expect(row.clients).to.be.an('array');",
              "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('reservations_count');",
              "  });",
              "});",
              "pm.test('Total reservations matches sum per car', function () {",
              "  const sum = j.data.cars.reduce(function (acc, c) { return acc + (c.reservations_count || 0); }, 0);",
              "  pm.expect(sum).to.eql(j.data.reservations_count);",
              "});",
              "if (j.data && j.data.id) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('trip_id', String(j.data.id));",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "bearer",
          "bearer": [
            { "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }
          ]
        },
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"date\": \"{{trip_date}}\",\n  \"time_id\": {{trip_time_id}},\n  \"cars\": [\n    {\n      \"captain_id\": {{captain_id}},\n      \"car_id\": {{car_id}},\n      \"status\": \"planned\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"captain_id\": {{captain_id_2}},\n      \"car_id\": {{car_id_2}},\n      \"status\": \"planned\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/trips"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3b) Create Trip (1 car only)",
      "description": "Use when the pending group is small enough for a single vehicle. Same prerequisites as step 3.",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 201', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Single car in response', function () { pm.expect(j.data.cars.length).to.eql(1); });",
              "if (j.data && j.data.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('trip_id', String(j.data.id)); }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "bearer",
          "bearer": [
            { "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }
          ]
        },
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"date\": \"{{trip_date}}\",\n  \"time_id\": {{trip_time_id}},\n  \"cars\": [\n    {\n      \"captain_id\": {{captain_id}},\n      \"car_id\": {{car_id}},\n      \"status\": \"planned\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/trips"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4) List Trips",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Trips list exists', function () { pm.expect(j.data).to.be.an('array'); });",
              "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('trip_id') && Array.isArray(j.data) && j.data.length) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('trip_id', String(j.data[0].id));",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "bearer",
          "bearer": [
            { "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }
          ]
        },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/trips?per_page={{per_page}}"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5) Show Trip",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Has trip object', function () { pm.expect(j.data).to.be.an('object'); });",
              "pm.test('Correct trip returned', function () { pm.expect(String(j.data.id)).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('trip_id')); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "bearer",
          "bearer": [
            { "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }
          ]
        },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/trips/{{trip_id}}"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6) Update Trip (>24h rule)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200 or 422', function () {",
              "  pm.expect([200, 422]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "bearer",
          "bearer": [
            { "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }
          ]
        },
        "method": "PATCH",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"in_progress\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/trips/{{trip_id}}"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "7) Delete Trip (>24h rule)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200 or 422', function () {",
              "  pm.expect([200, 422]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "bearer",
          "bearer": [
            { "key": "token", "value": "{{admin_token}}", "type": "string" }
          ]
        },
        "method": "DELETE",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/trips/{{trip_id}}"
      }
    }
  ]
}
